Hon. Benjamin Kalu has been elected the deputy speaker of the 10th House of Representatives. He emerged deputy speaker unopposed. Kalu, from Abia State, was nominated by Hon.  Jimi Benson, a member representing Ikorodu federal constituency of Lagos. The nomination was seconded by Khadijat Abba-Ibrahim, representing Damaturu Federal Constituency of Yobe State. Kalu succeeds Hon Idris Wase as deputy speaker. Details later…